{"title_page": "H.R. College of Commerce and Economics", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2015}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=August 2015}}\n{{Infobox university\n| name = HR College\n| image_name = \n| image_size = \n| established = 1960\n| motto = 'Where ideas goes nowhere'\n| president = Anil Harish\n| city = [[Mumbai]]\n| state = [[Maharashtra]]\n| postalcode = 400020\n| country = [[India]]\n| affiliations = [[University of Mumbai]]<p>[[Maharashtra State Board of Secondary and Higher Secondary Education]]\n| website = {{url|http://www.hrcollege.edu}}\n| logo = https://images.app.goo.gl/mDf6HrocdrDwi7YLA\n| type = [[Public]]\n| language = English\n}}\n[[File:H R College.jpg|thumb|Entrance to the college]]\n'''Hassaram Rijhumal College of Commerce and Economics''', commonly known as HR College, is a premi\u00e9r college located in [[Churchgate]], [[Mumbai]]. It is run by the [[Hyderabad (Sind) National Collegiate Board|Hyderabad (Sindh) National Collegiate Board]] and is affiliated to the [[University of Mumbai]]. \n\nIt was the second college in Maharashtra (after [[Kishinchand Chellaram College|KC College, Churchgate]]) to be accredited \u2018A\u2019 grade with a score of 87.95% by the NAAC ([[National Assessment & Accreditation Council]]) under the revised scheme in 2002. <ref> https://www.hrcollege.edu/college-profile/</ref>\n\nIt is located adjacent to [[Kishinchand Chellaram College]] and shares a building with the [[K C Law College, Mumbai|K. C. Law College]].\n\n==College Leadership==\nDr. [[Indu Shahani]], a noted academicians and former [[Sheriff of Mumbai]], is a former principal of HR College.\n\nCurrently, Prof. [[Chartered accountant|CA]]. Parag Thakkar is the principal in-charge of the college. He is also head of Department (HoD) of [[Accounting|Accountancy]] for degree college.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/mumbai/Shahani-quits-HR-after-25-yrs-says-lectures-keep-her-going/articleshow/53134620.cms|title=Shahani quits HR after 25 yrs, says lectures keep her going|last=|first=|date=|website=|access-date=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.freepressjournal.in/education/an-education-institution-should-be-supportive-of-the-students-says-hr-college-principal/955664|title=\"An education institution should be supportive of the students\", says ..|last=|first=|date=|website=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n==Courses==\nThe courses offered by the institute can be broadly classified into two categories; Junior college degrees & Senior college degrees. \n\nJunior college degrees includes 11th grade (FYJC) & 12th grade (SYJC) courses. For this, it is affiliated to [[Maharashtra State Board of Secondary and Higher Secondary Education|Maharashtra State education board]]. This includes the High School passing certificate (Class 12 certificate).<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.hrcollege.edu/junior-college-2/|title=HR College; Junior College courses|last=|first=|date=|website=hrcollege.edu|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>  \n\nSenior college degrees offered by the institute include courses such as [[Bachelor of Commerce|BCom]], [[Bachelor of Management Studies|BMS]], BBI, BAF, BMM, BFM and [[Bachelor of Vocational Education|BVoc.]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.hrcollege.edu/degree-college-3/|title=HR College; Degree College courses|last=|first=|date=|website=hrcollege.edu|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref> For this, it was affiliated to [[University of Mumbai]]. \n\nIn 2019, it was announced that HR College will be part of the second cluster university in [[Mumbai]] called [[Hyderabad (Sind) National Collegiate Board|H(S)NC cluster university]]. This cluster university would also include (and be led by) [[Kishinchand Chellaram College|KC College]]. They were officialy suppose to become part of the cluster university from academic year 2020-21.\n\n==Notable alumni==\n<!-- Please ensure entries are added in alphabetical order of surname/family name, then subsorted by forename(s)-->\n*[[Sooraj Barjatya]], film director\n*[[Arjun Bijlani]], actor<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.colorstv.com/in/news/5-things-you-didnt-know-about-arjun-bijlani-matsh-2774.html|title=5 things you didn't know about Arjun Bijlani #MATSH|work=Colors TV|date=25 March 2015 |last=Arora |first=Prerna |accessdate=27 December 2016}}</ref>\n*[[Shantanu Maheshwari]]\n*[[Kumar Mangalam Birla]], businessman<ref name=\"hrcollege1\">{{cite web |url=http://www.hrcollege.edu/web/alumni.htm |title=HRCollege of Commerce & Economics |publisher=Hrcollege.edu |date=2005-11-06 |access-date=2013-01-03 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130107200731/http://www.hrcollege.edu/web/alumni.htm |archive-date=7 January 2013 |df=dmy-all }}{{Third-party-inline|date=January 2013}}</ref>{{better source|date=December 2016}}\n*[[Kishore Biyani]], businessman<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.thenational.ae/business/the-making-of-indias-retail-king |first=Armina |last=Ligaya |work=The National |date=15 October 2009 |title=The making of India's retail King |accessdate=2017-05-12}}</ref>\n*[[Aarti Chhabria]], actress<ref name=\"hrcollege1\"/>\n*[[Varun Dhawan]], Celebrated actor\n*[[Tanaaz Irani]], actress\n*[[Karan Johar]], Noted film director<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.filmibeat.com/bollywood/news/2009/karan-nostalgia-college-220909.html |title=Karan Johar goes back to college |website=[[Filmibeat]] |publisher=Greynium Information Technologies Pvt. Ltd. |date=22 September 2009 |accessdate=27 December 2016}}</ref>\n*[[Karan Jotwani]], model & actor\n*[[Kunal Jaisingh]], actor\n*[[Ranbir Kapoor]], Celebrated actor<ref>{{cite news |last1=Gupta |first1=Priya |title=I have quit smoking as it also lowers your mojo: Ranbir Kapoor |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/news-interviews/I-have-quit-smoking-as-it-also-lowers-your-mojo-Ranbir-Kapoor/articleshow/16612605.cms?referral=PM |accessdate=23 September 2018 |work=Enter